WEBVTT

00:00.667 --> 00:02.801
Clarence:
Previously on "Clarence,"

00:02.836 --> 00:04.903
Mom and Chad wanted
to have a gigantic sleepover,

00:04.938 --> 00:07.539
and I did, too.
So we invited everyone in town.

00:07.574 --> 00:10.409
But then, um,
the power went off,

00:10.444 --> 00:14.346
and, 'cause, um, because --
because of -- of ghosts.

00:14.381 --> 00:15.748
Aah!

00:15.783 --> 00:17.916
So no one could come,
except for Jeff.

00:17.951 --> 00:20.919
But before Jeff got to my house,
I decided to go out,

00:20.954 --> 00:23.922
and I had to get
some, uh, ghost grenades.

00:23.957 --> 00:28.427
Oh, and Jeff thinks
his kite made the power go out.

00:28.462 --> 00:29.428
[ Remote clicks ]

00:29.463 --> 00:31.230
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:33.700 --> 00:36.769
♪ I don't care what you say ♪

00:36.804 --> 00:39.138
[ Ominous music playing ]

00:47.314 --> 00:49.615
Jeff: [ Thinking ]
<i>Why, Jellyman? Why?</i>

00:49.650 --> 00:53.786
♪♪

00:53.821 --> 00:55.754
Hey, Mare,
- have you seen the candles?

00:55.789 --> 00:57.356
Chad, I got 'em right here.

00:57.391 --> 01:00.125
<i>If they go outside,</i>
<i>they'll see it was my fault.</i>

01:00.160 --> 01:02.594
<i>Don't let them go outside.</i>
<i>Then they won't see.</i>

01:02.629 --> 01:04.363
<i>H-How hard could it be?</i>

01:04.398 --> 01:06.131
[ Laughs evilly ]

01:06.166 --> 01:08.967
I wonder where Clarence went.
Maybe we should check outside.

01:09.002 --> 01:11.603
-Hey, Jeff, you want a candle?
-Aah! Don't go outside.

01:11.638 --> 01:12.905
-Uh...
-Um...

01:12.940 --> 01:14.973
Because it's raining.
You'll get wet.

01:15.008 --> 01:17.810
Okay...
Is Clarence out there?

01:17.845 --> 01:21.280
Um, yes, but
he said he'd be right back.

01:21.315 --> 01:23.115
He's playing...

01:23.150 --> 01:25.250
I guess that's okay.
He's a free-range kid.

01:25.285 --> 01:27.219
-Ha!
-[ Laughs nervously ] Yeah.

01:27.254 --> 01:29.988
That Clarence,
always going outside.

01:30.023 --> 01:32.124
[ Laughs ]
Yeah, he sure is.

01:32.159 --> 01:34.626
[ Laughs ]
I'm like, "No, Clarence.

01:34.661 --> 01:36.762
I don't want
to play in the rain.

01:36.797 --> 01:38.263
I'll get your house
all muddy."

01:38.298 --> 01:40.065
Aww, that's so thoughtful
of you, Jeff.

01:40.100 --> 01:42.334
-I like this kid.
-Chad, run to Larry's house

01:42.369 --> 01:43.769
and see if his power
is out, too.

01:43.804 --> 01:45.771
Oh, a-a-and see if he has
extra flashlights.

01:45.806 --> 01:47.806
No need to go outside.

01:47.841 --> 01:49.675
[ Panting ]

01:49.710 --> 01:51.577
I stashed flashlights here
months ago,

01:51.612 --> 01:53.312
in case of emergency.

01:53.347 --> 01:56.682
Kid knows how to stash.

01:56.717 --> 01:58.283
All right, I'm impressed.

01:58.318 --> 02:00.118
Well, I guess we should,
uh, get started

02:00.153 --> 02:02.521
cleaning Clarence's
couch fort disaster, huh?

02:02.556 --> 02:04.423
Wait, Mary. Look.

02:04.458 --> 02:08.961
♪♪

02:08.996 --> 02:11.930
Um, I-I just can't stand
a mess like this.

02:11.965 --> 02:13.632
-[ Chuckles ]
-I like this.

02:13.667 --> 02:17.469
He's like a kid
robot butler.

02:17.504 --> 02:20.005
And that's
how you prevent

02:20.040 --> 02:22.808
greasy film spots
from forming.

02:22.843 --> 02:24.209
I could watch this
all day.

02:24.244 --> 02:26.278
Oh, hey, did you check
the fuse box yet?

02:26.313 --> 02:28.680
That's, like, the first thing
I should've done.

02:28.715 --> 02:29.781
Come on, Chad.

02:29.816 --> 02:31.884
-[ Gasping ] Please wait.
-Oh!

02:31.919 --> 02:33.218
What is it, clean boy?

02:33.253 --> 02:35.654
I-I-I already checked
the fuse box,

02:35.689 --> 02:37.189
and everything was fine,

02:37.224 --> 02:39.958
so the problem must be
at the electrical company

02:39.993 --> 02:43.862
or somewhere
else really far away.

02:43.897 --> 02:46.698
-You already checked?
-Now I'm going to go...

02:46.733 --> 02:49.201
organize your shoes.

02:49.236 --> 02:50.869
[ Panting ]

02:50.904 --> 02:53.138
-He's a helpful boy.
-I love Clarence,

02:53.173 --> 02:56.308
but having a kid who likes to
clean is a nice change of pace.

02:56.343 --> 02:58.410
♪ Ahh ♪

02:58.445 --> 03:01.480
Yeah.
- New Clarence is awesome.

03:01.515 --> 03:04.049
[ Panting ]

03:06.887 --> 03:08.253
[ Thunder crashes ]

03:08.288 --> 03:10.088
And did you see how fast
he cleaned up?

03:10.123 --> 03:11.490
Not, like,
cutting-corners cleaning,

03:11.525 --> 03:12.991
he was really scrubbing.

03:13.026 --> 03:15.093
I'm afraid of what chemicals
he breathed in, actually.

03:15.128 --> 03:17.229
Yeah, I'm writing a song
for the little guy.

03:17.264 --> 03:18.263
[ Guitar strums ]

03:18.298 --> 03:20.799
Wish I could plug
this baby in, though.

03:22.803 --> 03:24.002
Have you seen Jeff?

03:24.037 --> 03:25.437
-Hello.
-Aah!

03:25.472 --> 03:27.005
Jeff, you scared us.

03:27.040 --> 03:28.373
Mary.
[ Chuckles ]

03:28.408 --> 03:31.743
I took the liberty
- of making you a chore wheel.

03:31.778 --> 03:33.178
Uh, thanks, I guess.

03:33.213 --> 03:35.113
I mean, I don't forget about the
chores.

03:35.148 --> 03:37.916
I'm just --
I'm a very busy...

03:37.951 --> 03:40.352
independent woman.
So, that's --

03:40.387 --> 03:42.054
I'm not a messy --
I'm not a slob.

03:42.089 --> 03:44.890
[ Chuckles ] Clearly. But it's
the thought that counts,

03:44.925 --> 03:47.426
so thank you very much, Jeff.
That's very nice.

03:47.461 --> 03:51.597
Um, anything interesting
happen at school this week?

03:51.632 --> 03:53.899
I do have
a good anecdote.

03:53.934 --> 03:55.634
So, I was on my way
to school.

03:55.669 --> 03:58.570
It was a pleasant
morning indeed.

03:58.605 --> 03:59.871
[<i> Duck quacks</i> ]

03:59.906 --> 04:01.607
"How trivial."

04:01.642 --> 04:05.210
Fixing my sandal, I noticed
this trail of strange red liquid

04:05.245 --> 04:07.145
leading straight
to these bushes.

04:07.180 --> 04:10.148
Can you believe it? I almost
stepped in some unknown --

04:10.183 --> 04:12.651
Jeffery, what was the liquid?
Was it from, like, guts?

04:12.686 --> 04:14.086
Yeah, where was it
coming from?

04:14.121 --> 04:16.254
Oh, I don't know.
- The -- The point of the story

04:16.289 --> 04:18.323
is that I was lucky enough
not to get involved.

04:18.358 --> 04:20.892
And what's better
than a good luck story?

04:20.927 --> 04:22.127
[ Thunder crashes ]
Ha.

04:22.162 --> 04:23.495
Yeah, Mary,
it kind of reminds me

04:23.530 --> 04:25.397
of the time Clarence,
he was making a kite.

04:25.432 --> 04:27.399
And it ended up
- getting stuck in the tree.

04:27.434 --> 04:29.334
And we thought Clarence
was missing the whole time,

04:29.369 --> 04:31.303
but he was stuck
in the tree, too.

04:31.338 --> 04:32.137
[ Laughs ]

04:32.172 --> 04:34.306
[ Electricity crackling ]

04:34.341 --> 04:36.341
[ Poink! ]

04:36.376 --> 04:38.944
Hey, I know.
- Let's play "The Clarence Show."

04:38.979 --> 04:40.646
That's one
of Clarence's favorites.

04:40.681 --> 04:42.781
The C-Clarence show?

04:42.816 --> 04:44.916
[ Both laugh ]

04:44.951 --> 04:46.685
Mary: Okay. Shh, shh.
Okay, okay.

04:46.720 --> 04:48.120
Okay.
[ Clears throat ]

04:48.155 --> 04:50.956
[ As Chad ]
Uh, I'm hungry.

04:50.991 --> 04:52.524
[ Normal voice ]
Jeff, that's your cue.

04:52.559 --> 04:55.027
[ As Mary ] Oh, I guess
with no Clarence around,

04:55.062 --> 04:57.496
-we can have some fun.
-[ As Chad ] I'll say.

04:57.531 --> 05:01.133
[ Both chuckle, smooch ]

05:01.168 --> 05:04.136
Oh, hey.
Uh, duh, I'm hungry.

05:04.171 --> 05:07.439
Are you hungry,
too, Clarence?

05:07.474 --> 05:08.507
Sure.

05:08.542 --> 05:11.710
[ Chuckling ]
- How does toot soup sound?

05:11.745 --> 05:15.047
[ Chuckling ]
My favorite.

05:15.082 --> 05:18.383
Is that a joke?
- Soup made from human flatulence?

05:18.418 --> 05:21.053
That's disgusting.

05:21.088 --> 05:22.554
Uh, well, uh...

05:22.589 --> 05:25.490
That's okay,
because we've got to, uh...

05:25.525 --> 05:29.695
Go into outer space
and fight the evil alien king?

05:29.730 --> 05:33.065
Uh, duh, uh, yeah,
that sounds fun.

05:33.100 --> 05:36.568
Clarence, are you coming?

05:36.603 --> 05:38.037
No.

05:39.506 --> 05:42.874
[ Normal voice ] All right.
Well, that was...fun.

05:42.909 --> 05:44.476
May I be excused?

05:44.511 --> 05:46.511
Yeah, sure.

05:46.546 --> 05:49.147
[ Sighs ]
I don't want Jeff anymore.

05:49.182 --> 05:51.183
I'm starting to get worried
about Clarence.

05:51.218 --> 05:53.385
I wonder where he went.

05:53.420 --> 05:56.555
Just arranging these knives
from dullest to sharpest.

05:56.590 --> 05:57.689
[ Laughs nervously ]

05:57.724 --> 05:59.991
Kind of spooky in here.

06:00.026 --> 06:04.062
♪♪

06:04.097 --> 06:06.031
[ Grunting ]

06:06.066 --> 06:08.667
Okay, kiddo.
- You've been such a big help.

06:08.702 --> 06:10.235
Huh?
[ Grunting ]

06:10.270 --> 06:12.003
All right,
now it's time to relax.

06:12.038 --> 06:15.374
Come on.
- Park that keister, meister.

06:18.779 --> 06:20.879
Go ahead, pig out.

06:23.250 --> 06:25.117
[ Gasps ]

06:25.152 --> 06:27.519
Whoopsie. Guess I'll have
to clean my mess.

06:27.554 --> 06:30.455
Don't worry about it.
Clarence does this all the time.

06:30.490 --> 06:32.791
There. This way,
it doesn't go to waste.

06:32.826 --> 06:35.794
-Drink up. Come on.
-[ Gags ] Oh, no.

06:35.829 --> 06:38.463
[ Thump ]
Chad: Ow. Just stubbed my toe.

06:38.498 --> 06:39.865
I can't see anything.

06:39.900 --> 06:43.034
[ Sighs ] This power outage
is gonna kill him, I swear.

06:43.069 --> 06:45.036
[ Thunder crashes ]

06:45.071 --> 06:46.304
I am so sorry.

06:46.339 --> 06:47.806
Oh, it's not your fault,
sweetie.

06:47.841 --> 06:50.108
Just enjoy
your cookies and milk.

06:50.143 --> 06:51.810
[ Inhales deeply ]

06:51.845 --> 06:52.978
[ Chuckles nervously ]

06:53.013 --> 06:56.281
[ Gulping ]

06:56.316 --> 06:57.949
[ Gags ]

06:57.984 --> 07:01.620
[ Munching ]

07:01.655 --> 07:03.655
[ Burps ]

07:03.690 --> 07:04.823
Pretty good, huh?

07:04.858 --> 07:05.991
[ Thunder crashes ]

07:06.026 --> 07:07.225
That was a big one.

07:07.260 --> 07:08.493
Okay, it's time
to find Clarence.

07:08.528 --> 07:11.062
No! H-He said
he would be right back.

07:11.097 --> 07:12.664
Why won't you believe me?

07:12.699 --> 07:13.965
Whoa, calm down.

07:14.000 --> 07:16.067
Oh, I-I know.
I'll sing you a song.

07:16.102 --> 07:17.502
Sometimes when Clarence
gets worked up,

07:17.537 --> 07:19.004
-I'll -- I'll sing him --
-I'm not Clarence.

07:19.039 --> 07:21.940
My name is Jeff,
and I just want to clean up.

07:21.975 --> 07:24.776
All right, all right,
whatever you want.

07:24.811 --> 07:26.077
What's he up to?

07:26.112 --> 07:27.646
Jeff:
He said he'd be right back.

07:27.681 --> 07:29.815
R-Right, Clarence? Uh --

07:29.850 --> 07:31.483
Oh, this is all my fault.

07:31.518 --> 07:33.418
Clarence is gone,
and the power is out.

07:33.453 --> 07:34.853
What have I done?

07:34.888 --> 07:37.255
[ Distorted ]
Jeff. I'm lost, Jeff.

07:37.290 --> 07:39.090
Clarence.
W-Where'd you go?

07:39.125 --> 07:41.827
I'm lost,
- and it's all because of you.

07:41.862 --> 07:43.528
I have no way
of contacting you --

07:43.563 --> 07:46.031
[ Gasps ]
Huh?

07:46.066 --> 07:47.532
Of course.

07:47.567 --> 07:50.168
Mary: I'm sure Clarence is fine.
We just need to make a plan.

07:50.203 --> 07:52.103
Quiet.
You think he heard us?

07:52.138 --> 07:54.172
First we check outside.
[ Thunder crashes ]

07:54.207 --> 07:55.207
There you are.

07:55.242 --> 07:56.942
-Aah!
-Aah!

07:56.977 --> 07:59.544
Both: Huh? I never thought
to radio Clarence.

07:59.579 --> 08:01.346
He's usually the one
calling me.

08:01.381 --> 08:03.281
We can find out
where he is.

08:03.316 --> 08:05.817
J. Proper to Clarence-saurus.
[ Beep, static ]

08:05.852 --> 08:08.553
J. Proper to Clarence-saurus,
do you read me?

08:08.588 --> 08:09.855
Clarence:<i> J-Jeff?</i>

08:09.890 --> 08:11.890
Clarence!
Clarence, are you okay?

08:11.925 --> 08:13.825
Clarence! Stupid thing.

08:13.860 --> 08:15.126
-Aah!
-Hey.

08:15.161 --> 08:17.229
-Oh, I'm sorry.
-I can't wait any longer.

08:17.264 --> 08:18.897
We need to go look for him.

08:18.932 --> 08:21.733
♪♪

08:21.768 --> 08:23.902
Gonna need that flashlight.
Calculator --

08:23.937 --> 08:26.571
Oh, my gosh. It's all my fault
Clarence got lost.

08:26.606 --> 08:29.674
What do you mean, "it's all
your fault Clarence got lost"?

08:29.709 --> 08:30.909
Huh?

08:30.944 --> 08:32.911
I mean...

08:32.946 --> 08:34.846
friendship is like --

08:34.881 --> 08:36.147
like an egg.

08:36.182 --> 08:38.083
Yeah. Th-That's right.
A-An egg.

08:38.118 --> 08:40.485
You've got to hold it gently
in your hands.

08:40.520 --> 08:42.087
Sometimes the mama bird
attacks you.

08:42.122 --> 08:44.055
[ Squawks ]
And you drop the egg.

08:44.090 --> 08:47.025
It smashes on the ground,
and you see it's -- it's broken.

08:47.060 --> 08:48.493
Stupid. Stupid. Stupid.

08:48.528 --> 08:51.263
You can't put the egg
back together again. No.

08:51.298 --> 08:53.231
Too many pieces.
Too many --

08:53.266 --> 08:55.400
[ Thunder crashes ]

08:55.435 --> 08:57.535
I mean, he could be anywhere.
He could be in a ditch.

08:57.570 --> 09:00.105
He could be in the dirt. I mean,
he's into a lot of hobbies.

09:00.140 --> 09:03.909
Mary:
- Chad, that is not helping.

09:03.944 --> 09:07.078
[ Grunting ]

09:07.113 --> 09:10.181
Clarence. Here, boy.

09:10.216 --> 09:11.516
We got tacos.

09:11.551 --> 09:13.585
Uh, I think you should
turn left up here.

09:13.620 --> 09:15.553
That's a one way street, Jeff.
I can't.

09:15.588 --> 09:18.056
-Are you sure? Because --
-We can't go that way.

09:18.091 --> 09:20.725
Uh, hey, little guy,
where are you?

09:20.760 --> 09:22.527
[ As Clarence ]
I'm probably lost forever.

09:22.562 --> 09:24.129
[ Normal voice ]
Don't say that!

09:24.164 --> 09:25.797
I'll find you, boy!

09:25.832 --> 09:27.966
-[ Sobbing ]
-Chad.

09:28.001 --> 09:30.969
Sorry.
- Here, Jeff, you take him.

09:31.004 --> 09:33.972
Wait, Jeff?

09:34.007 --> 09:36.574
Why won't anyone pick me up?

09:36.609 --> 09:38.109
Ohh! Oh, no!

09:38.144 --> 09:39.444
[ Grunting ]

09:39.479 --> 09:40.912
I'm going to tell on you.

09:40.947 --> 09:42.614
Go ahead,<i> Chad.</i>

09:42.649 --> 09:44.149
-Mary!
-Quit it, you two.

09:44.184 --> 09:45.650
[ Alarm blaring in distance ]

09:45.685 --> 09:47.819
Maybe there's something
about Clarence on the news.

09:47.854 --> 09:50.722
Mayor:<i> This is a severe weather</i>
<i>warning for Aberdale.</i>

09:50.757 --> 09:53.058
<i>Please defer to</i>
<i>your local safety officer --</i>

09:53.093 --> 09:55.427
Computer:<i> Melanie Baker --</i>
I can't listen to the news.

09:55.462 --> 09:57.562
It gives me anxiety.
Could you turn it off?

09:57.597 --> 09:58.964
-Turn it off.
<i>-Emergency broadcast.</i>

09:58.999 --> 10:00.899
-Could you turn it off?
-Quiet, I can't hear it.

10:00.934 --> 10:02.233
Turn it off. Turn it off.

10:02.268 --> 10:03.601
-Quiet.
-That's it.

10:03.636 --> 10:05.437
[ Tires screech ]

10:07.440 --> 10:09.274
I've had enough.
I need both of you alert

10:09.309 --> 10:11.543
and looking for Clarence,
understood?

10:15.382 --> 10:17.349
Do you want me
- to turn the news back on?

10:17.384 --> 10:19.985
It's not gonna help.

10:20.020 --> 10:21.119
Can I see?

10:21.154 --> 10:23.188
Don't hurt him.

10:23.223 --> 10:24.990
[ Sighs ] Okay.
Come on, Clarence.

10:25.025 --> 10:28.360
Talk to me, buddy.
Talk to me.

10:28.395 --> 10:30.495
[ As Clarence ] Hey, Jeff.
It's Clarence.

10:30.530 --> 10:32.964
I like pillow forts
and sleepovers.

10:32.999 --> 10:35.500
♪♪

10:35.535 --> 10:36.968
And you should
come over, too.

10:37.003 --> 10:39.537
Both: I'll get you your favorite
raisin slurpy drink.

10:39.572 --> 10:43.208
Don't worry, the sleepover will
be just you and me, buddy.

10:43.243 --> 10:47.045
Wow, that was really good.

10:47.080 --> 10:49.114
-I know where he is.
-What? Where?

10:49.149 --> 10:51.049
Head to Main Street.

10:51.084 --> 10:52.117
Ha!

10:52.152 --> 10:53.885
[ Tires squealing ]

10:53.920 --> 10:56.388
♪♪

10:56.423 --> 10:58.423
[ Thunder crashes ]

11:03.196 --> 11:04.496
♪ Early to bed ♪

11:06.533 --> 11:08.367
♪ Early to rise ♪

11:10.103 --> 11:12.337
♪ Pickin' my nose ♪
